\b\fs20 \cf0 Skip navigation links/ & Landmarks
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 Provide direct access to page content. Use the document's semantic structure for built-in keyboard navigation. New HTML 5 tags are particularly useful.
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Well-planned , consistent  navigation 
\b0 Users like consistency, keep it in the same place, let them know where they are, keep it looking the same.
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Links
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 are the stepping stones of the internet. Tell users where they are going and warn them of 
\b context changes.
\b0\fs24 \
\

\fs20 Use 
\b unique
\b0  
\b meaningful words
\b0  for linked text. Careful use of the title attribute \'96 DRY principle is a good practice here.
\fs24 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Text Alternatives
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 Provide meaningful text alternatives for all content images. This is the required
\b  alt attribute. 
\b0 Use 
\b null-alt
\b0  appropriately.
\fs24 \
\

\fs20 For 
\b charts or complex images
\b0 , use your judgement. May need supplementary content (which could potentially benefit all users). Main thing is to maintain the meaning of the document. If the document is rendered meaningless without the image or with only a brief description, the user needs more.
\fs24 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Don't rely on colour alone
\b0  to communicate meaning information. Use mark-up, text, context and non-colour style.
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Choose colours wisely.
\b0  This does not mean do not use colour, it means be sure to not use confusing colours and to test your choices for sufficient contrast ratios. 
\i\b Unsure test your choices. The Brewer Palette may be useful.
\i0\b0\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Choose sufficient contrast
\b0  between foreground and background colour by testing it.
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 CSS for layout  & consistency-
\b0  all 
\b presentation needs.
\b0  Using 
\b CSS & HTML together properly
\b0  will give you the biggest bang in making your content accessible and easier to maintain.
\fs24 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Simplify Tables
\b0  wherever possible. Use the rich set of table mark-up available to make your tables readable (this helps in styling to for visual readers, too).
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Use Caption
\b0  to introduce the content of your data table instead of a paragraph or heading.
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 Use 
\b tables only for tabular data 
\b0 \'96 not content layout!
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Forms
\b0  are complex & challenging; dynamic interactive functioning content.
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 Like tables, 
\b keep it simple 
\b0 \'96 don't ask for data you don't need. Most legal cases have happened around in-accessible forms & tables.
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Use labels
\b0  for form controls and 
\b associate
\b0  them to the control.
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Group form controls. 
\b0 There is a rich set of tags for creating meaning in forms; Legend, fieldset, optgroup, etc. Also helps with styling \'96 extremely important for visual users, too.
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Clear error identification
\b0  
\i (don't rely on colour alone).
\i0\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Intuitive error handling. 
\b0 Need to work through this carefully. Including clearly telling the user they succeeded.
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Leave control with user
\b0  (enough time, rechecking  & submitting).
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 (Note: Most legal cases have happened around in-accessible forms & tables.)
\fs24 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 No auto-play 
\b0 of anything. Leave control with user
\b  
\b0 (samurai mantra).
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\fs20 \cf0 Provide open or closed 
\b captions 
\b0 for audio and video.
\fs24 \
\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab709

\b\fs20 \cf0 Audio description for v
\b0 ideo that cannot be understood by the soundtrack alone: (open or closed).
\fs24 \
\

\b\fs20 Transcripts
\b0  in some cases makes better sense than captions (podcasts of conversations).
\fs24 \
